          <ol class="sw-step-list" data-1g-steps>
            <li data-1g-step="1"><strong>1. EG.</strong> Each adjacent pair emits matter–photon Bell pairs; the photons meet at a midpoint photonic BSM; a successful herald collapses the two distant matter qubits into a Bell pair</li>
            <li data-1g-step="2"><strong>2. 1st ES.</strong> Parallel matter-qubit Bell measurements at R₁ and R₃ extend the entanglement to A↔R₂ and R₂↔B; the 2-bit outcomes travel back to A and B</li>
            <li data-1g-step="3"><strong>3. 2nd ES.</strong> A final Bell measurement at R₂ delivers a single A↔B Bell pair; its 2-bit outcome travels to one endpoint to fix the Pauli correction</li>
            <li data-1g-step="4"><strong>4. Result.</strong> One long A↔B Bell pair ready to consume — for teleportation, for QKD key extraction, or for any other Bell-pair-consuming protocol</li>
          </ol>

          <figcaption>
            Every BSM in this diagram broadcasts <strong>two classical bits</strong>
            (orange herald in EG; orange travelling pulses in the swap rows) and the
            matter qubits must hold their state until those bits arrive — the local
            Pauli correction can only be applied once the outcome is known. The reach
            of a 1G chain is therefore bounded not by photon loss alone but by how
            long each memory can hold while the slowest classical message is in
            flight. <br/><br/>
            <strong>Where the swap bits go.</strong> Physically, either qubit in a
            swapped Bell pair can carry the Pauli correction, so the bits can flow
            either way. The convention drawn here — and the one most 1G protocols
            adopt — is to <strong>compose all corrections at one endpoint</strong>
            (B in this figure), so every swap's 2-bit outcome flows rightward and B
            applies a single composed Pauli at the end. Sending some bits to A and
            some to B would work too, but composing at one end keeps the bookkeeping
            simpler. Each row is a <em>repeat-until-success</em> loop — EG retries
            until the herald fires, every swap retries until its BSM succeeds
            (currently shown deterministic; loss retries can be toggled on).
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <Callout label="Why fidelity drops with chain length">
          <p>
            Each Bell pair starts at some fidelity below 1 — heralded entanglement is
            never perfect. Each BSM at a relay is also imperfect, and each Pauli
            correction sees noise from the classical-message latency relative to the
            memory's coherence time. The end-to-end Bell pair's fidelity is roughly the
            product of the per-link fidelities, multiplied by the BSM and memory
            contributions, so chains of swaps degrade fidelity multiplicatively. This
            is why distillation matters at scale — it counters the multiplicative loss
            by spending throughput on cleaner pairs.
          </p>
          <p>
            The first multi-node demo with this pattern is Pompili et al. 2021: a
            three-node NV-centre network — Alice, Bob, and Charlie — all sitting in
            the same lab at QuTech (Delft), with a maximum inter-node distance of
            <strong>7 metres</strong>. Charlie sits between Alice and Bob and acts as
            the swapping relay, demonstrating on-demand entanglement distribution
            between the non-neighbouring endpoints. The point isn't reach — it's that
            the protocol stack (entanglement generation, swap, fidelity reporting,
            classical signalling) ran end-to-end on a real
            platform <SourceNote id="pompili-science-2021" />.
          </p>
          <p>
            Successive milestones from the same era:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Hermans et al. 2022</strong> — same Delft 3-node hardware, now
              running <strong>qubit teleportation</strong> through the middle node, not
              just entanglement distribution <SourceNote id="hermans-nature-2022" />.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Krutyanskiy et al. 2023</strong> — trapped-ion entanglement
              between two nodes over <strong>230 m</strong> of deployed urban fibre in
              Innsbruck, the first outdoor-fibre heralded
              demo <SourceNote id="krutyanskiy-prl-2023" />.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Knaut et al. 2024</strong> — two SiV-centre nodes at Harvard with
              telecom-O QFC, generating entanglement through a <strong>35 km</strong>
              loop of deployed Boston-area fibre at 17 dB total
              loss <SourceNote id="knaut-nature-2024" />.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            None of these are >3 nodes or km-scale across more than two; multi-node
            swapping chains over real fibre are still the open engineering frontier.
          </p>
        </Callout>
      </section>

      <section id="role" data-nav-section>
        <h2>Network role</h2>
        <p>
          Swapping is the primitive that turns a two-node Bell-pair distribution into a
          full network. The link-layer service ("deliver Bell pair (A, B) on demand")
          inside a single link is a generation problem; getting that pair across more
          than one link is a swapping problem. A repeater is, mechanically, a station
          that holds memories long enough to align swaps — the network engineering is
          all about which pairs to generate when, who fires first, and how to recover
          if any single link's heralding fails.
        </p>
        <p>
          Three follow-on subjects expand on this:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Distribution</strong> covers the link architectures (MM, SR, MS)
            that get a Bell pair onto a single link in the first place. See the
            <strong>distribution</strong> subject.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Distillation</strong> trades two noisy Bell pairs for one cleaner
            pair, restoring fidelity that chained swapping erodes. See the
            <strong>distillation</strong> subject.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Repeaters</strong> integrate generation, swapping, and distillation
            into the 1G / 2G / 3G architectural families. See the
            <strong>repeaters</strong> subject.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </Stack>
  </Center>
</Infographic>

<script type="module" is:inline>
  // Entanglement-swapping animation. Five phases:
  //   1. SETUP    — two Bell pairs (A↔A′, B′↔B) bright; BSM,
  //                 classical channel, bottom result dimmed.
  //   2. BSM      — A′ and B′ photons drop into the apparatus
  //                 along its two diagonals; clouds turn grey;
  //                 top entanglement lines fade; BSM brightens.
  //   3. SEND     — bits (a, b) slide right along the classical
  //                 channel to Bob.
  //   4. CORRECT  — Pauli badge drops onto B; bottom result row
  //                 brightens and the long A↔B wave traces in.
  //   5. HOLD     — everything visible, narrative lines stacked,
  //                 then a short fade-out before the cycle resets.
  const fig = document.querySelector("[data-sw]");
  if (fig) {
    const svg     = fig.querySelector("[data-sw-svg]");
    const aPrime  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-aprime]");
    const bPrime  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bprime]");
    const aCloud  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-aprime-cloud]");
    const bCloud  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bprime-cloud]");
    const pairAA  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-pair-aa]");
    const pairBB  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-pair-bb]");
    const pairAB  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-pair-ab]");
    const bsm     = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bsm]");
    const bits    = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bits]");
    const bitsTx  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-bits-text]");
    const lock    = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-lock]");
    const lockTx  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-lock-letter]");
    const result  = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-result]");
    const msg1    = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-msg1]");
    const msg2    = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-msg2]");
    const msg3    = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-msg3]");
    const msg4    = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-msg4]");
    const msg5    = svg.querySelector("[data-sw-msg5]");
    const stepEls = Array.from(fig.querySelectorAll("[data-sw-step]"));

    const AP_HOME = { x: 359, y: 60 };
    const BP_HOME = { x: 441, y: 60 };
    // BSM apparatus has its own viewBox 640×540 mapped to outer
    // rect (300, 62) → (500, 231). Inner→outer scaling factor:
    // x: 200/640 = 0.3125, y: 169/540 ≈ 0.3130.
    const SX = 200 / 640, SY = 169 / 540;
    const DET = {
      H1: { x: 300 + 130 * SX, y: 62 + 370 * SY },
      V1: { x: 300 + 250 * SX, y: 62 + 370 * SY },
      V2: { x: 300 + 390 * SX, y: 62 + 370 * SY },
      H2: { x: 300 + 510 * SX, y: 62 + 370 * SY },
    };
    const BS_POS = { x: 300 + 320 * SX, y: 62 + 180 * SY };
    const BIT_X_START = 475;
    const BIT_X_END   = 700;
    const LOCK_HOME   = { x: 750, y: 100 };

    // The four Bell-outcome variants. Click-pair labels match the
    // two photon paths through the apparatus; (a, b) is the 2-bit
    // code R sends to Bob; inv is the Pauli Bob applies. Cycled
    // through deterministically.
    const OUTCOMES = [
      { a: 0, b: 0, inv: "I",  clicks: ["H1", "H2"] },
      { a: 1, b: 0, inv: "Z",  clicks: ["V1", "V2"] },
      { a: 0, b: 1, inv: "X",  clicks: ["H1", "V1"] },
      { a: 1, b: 1, inv: "XZ", clicks: ["H1", "V2"] },
    ];
    let outcomeIndex = -1;
    let outcome = OUTCOMES[0];

    function setOpacity(el, op) { el.setAttribute("opacity", String(op)); }
    function setPos(g, x, y) { g.setAttribute("transform", `translate(${x} ${y})`); }
    function setBitsX(x) { bitsTx.setAttribute("x", String(x)); }
    function highlightStep(n) {
      for (const el of stepEls) {
        el.classList.toggle("sw-step--active", Number(el.dataset.swStep) === n);
      }
    }
    function ease(t) {
      return t < 0.5 ? 4*t*t*t : 1 - Math.pow(-2*t + 2, 3) / 2;
    }
    function twoLeg(start, mid, end, t) {
      if (t < 0.4) {
        const k = t / 0.4;
        return { x: start.x + (mid.x - start.x) * k, y: start.y + (mid.y - start.y) * k };
      }
      const k = (t - 0.4) / 0.6;
      return { x: mid.x + (end.x - mid.x) * k, y: mid.y + (end.y - mid.y) * k };
    }

    function pickCycleParams() {
      outcomeIndex = (outcomeIndex + 1) % OUTCOMES.length;
      outcome = OUTCOMES[outcomeIndex];
      bitsTx.textContent = `(${outcome.a}, ${outcome.b})`;
      lockTx.textContent = outcome.inv;
      aCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-teal)");
      bCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-teal)");
      setPos(aPrime, AP_HOME.x, AP_HOME.y);
      setPos(bPrime, BP_HOME.x, BP_HOME.y);
    }

    const reducedMotion = matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)").matches;

    if (reducedMotion) {
      pickCycleParams();
      setOpacity(aPrime, 0); setOpacity(bPrime, 0);
      setOpacity(pairAA, 0); setOpacity(pairBB, 0);
      setOpacity(bsm, 0.22);
      setOpacity(bits, 0); setOpacity(lock, 0);
      setOpacity(result, 1);
      pairAB.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0");
      setOpacity(msg1, 1); setOpacity(msg2, 1);
      setOpacity(msg3, 1); setOpacity(msg4, 1);
      setOpacity(msg5, 1);
      highlightStep(5);
    } else {
      const T_SETUP   = 1400;
      const T_DROP    = 1300;
      const T_MEASURE =  900;
      const T_SEND    = 1700;
      const T_UNLOCK  = 1100;
      const T_TRACE   = 1100;
      const T_HOLD    = 2600;
      const T_PAUSE   =  400;
      const T_TOTAL = T_SETUP + T_DROP + T_MEASURE + T_SEND + T_UNLOCK + T_TRACE + T_HOLD + T_PAUSE;

      let running = false;
      let cycleStart = 0;

      function frame(now) {
        if (!running) return;
        const elapsed = now - cycleStart;
        let t0 = T_SETUP;

        if (elapsed < t0) {
          // Phase 1 — setup
          highlightStep(1);
          setOpacity(aPrime, 1); setOpacity(bPrime, 1);
          setPos(aPrime, AP_HOME.x, AP_HOME.y);
          setPos(bPrime, BP_HOME.x, BP_HOME.y);
          aCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-teal)");
          bCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-teal)");
          setOpacity(pairAA, 0.95);
          setOpacity(pairBB, 0.95);
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.22);
          setOpacity(bits, 0);
          setOpacity(lock, 0);
          setOpacity(result, 0.18);
          pairAB.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "1");
          const t = elapsed / T_SETUP;
          setOpacity(msg1, Math.min(1, t * 2));
          setOpacity(msg2, 0); setOpacity(msg3, 0);
          setOpacity(msg4, 0); setOpacity(msg5, 0);
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_DROP)) {
          // Phase 2a — A′ and B′ drop into BSM apparatus
          highlightStep(2);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_DROP)) / T_DROP;
          const e = ease(t);
          const cClick = outcome.clicks[0];
          const bClick = outcome.clicks[1];
          const aEnd = DET[cClick];
          const bEnd = DET[bClick];
          const aPos = twoLeg(AP_HOME, BS_POS, aEnd, e);
          const bPos = twoLeg(BP_HOME, BS_POS, bEnd, e);
          setPos(aPrime, aPos.x, aPos.y);
          setPos(bPrime, bPos.x, bPos.y);
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.22 + 0.78 * Math.min(1, e * 1.5));
          setOpacity(pairAA, 0.95 * Math.max(0, 1 - e * 1.6));
          setOpacity(pairBB, 0.95 * Math.max(0, 1 - e * 1.6));
          if (e > 0.15) {
            aCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-spent)");
            bCloud.setAttribute("fill", "url(#sw-cloud-spent)");
          }
          setOpacity(msg1, 1);
          setOpacity(msg2, Math.min(1, e * 2));
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_MEASURE)) {
          // Phase 2b — measurement clicks
          highlightStep(2);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_MEASURE)) / T_MEASURE;
          const e = ease(t);
          setOpacity(aPrime, Math.max(0, 1 - e * 2));
          setOpacity(bPrime, Math.max(0, 1 - e * 2));
          setOpacity(pairAA, 0); setOpacity(pairBB, 0);
          setOpacity(bsm, 1);
          setOpacity(bits, Math.min(1, (e - 0.2) * 2));
          setBitsX(BIT_X_START);
          setOpacity(msg2, 1);
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_SEND)) {
          // Phase 3 — bits slide along classical channel
          highlightStep(3);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_SEND)) / T_SEND;
          setOpacity(aPrime, 0); setOpacity(bPrime, 0);
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.5);
          setOpacity(bits, 1);
          setBitsX(BIT_X_START + (BIT_X_END - BIT_X_START) * t);
          setOpacity(msg3, Math.min(1, t * 2));
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_UNLOCK)) {
          // Phase 4a — Pauli badge drops onto B
          highlightStep(4);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_UNLOCK)) / T_UNLOCK;
          const e = ease(t);
          setBitsX(BIT_X_END);
          setOpacity(bits, Math.max(0, 1 - e * 1.4));
          const ix_start = BIT_X_END, iy_start = 235;
          const ix_end = LOCK_HOME.x, iy_end = LOCK_HOME.y;
          const ix = ix_start + (ix_end - ix_start) * e;
          const iy = iy_start + (iy_end - iy_start) * e;
          setPos(lock, ix, iy);
          setOpacity(lock, Math.min(1, e * 2));
          setOpacity(msg4, Math.min(1, e * 2));
        } else if (elapsed < (t0 += T_TRACE)) {
          // Phase 4b — long A↔B Bell pair traces in
          highlightStep(5);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - T_TRACE)) / T_TRACE;
          const e = ease(t);
          setOpacity(result, 0.18 + 0.82 * e);
          pairAB.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", String(1 - e));
          setOpacity(lock, Math.max(0, 1 - e * 1.6));
          setOpacity(msg5, Math.min(1, (e - 0.3) * 2));
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.5 - 0.28 * e);
        } else if (elapsed < T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE) {
          // Phase 5 — hold final state
          highlightStep(5);
          setOpacity(result, 1);
          pairAB.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0");
          setOpacity(lock, 0);
          setOpacity(bsm, 0.22);
          setOpacity(msg1, 1); setOpacity(msg2, 1);
          setOpacity(msg3, 1); setOpacity(msg4, 1);
          setOpacity(msg5, 1);
        } else if (elapsed < T_TOTAL) {
          const t = (elapsed - (T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE)) / T_PAUSE;
          const a = Math.max(0, 1 - t);
          setOpacity(msg1, a); setOpacity(msg2, a);
          setOpacity(msg3, a); setOpacity(msg4, a);
          setOpacity(msg5, a);
        } else {
          cycleStart = now;
          pickCycleParams();
        }
        requestAnimationFrame(frame);
      }

      pickCycleParams();
      const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
        for (const entry of entries) {
          if (entry.isIntersecting && !running) {
            running = true;
            cycleStart = performance.now();
            pickCycleParams();
            requestAnimationFrame(frame);
          } else if (!entry.isIntersecting) {
            running = false;
          }
        }
      });
      observer.observe(fig);
    }
  }
</script>

<script type="module" is:inline>
  // Canonical 1G repeater animation. Four phases, walking down the four
  // rows of the stacked diagram so the reader sees time progression.
  // Each row remains visible (history) and dims to 0.45 once its phase
  // ends — the currently-active row stays at 1.0.
  //
  // Per-segment state machines are scaffolded so loss retries can be
  // toggled on by flipping CONFIG.lossEnabled (and dialling the success
  // probabilities below 1.0). With successP = 1.0 the cycle is
  // deterministic: every EG link heralds first try, every swap BSM
  // succeeds first try, and the animation plays linearly.
  const fig = document.querySelector("[data-1g]");
  if (fig) {
    const svg     = fig.querySelector("[data-1g-svg]");
    const rows    = [1, 2, 3, 4].map((n) => svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-row="${n}"]`));
    const photons = Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, i) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-photon="${i}"]`));
    const pbsmPulse = Array.from({ length: 4 }, (_, i) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-pbsm-pulse="${i}"]`));
    const heralds = Array.from({ length: 4 }, (_, i) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-herald="${i}"]`));
    const bmR1    = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r1]");
    const bmR3    = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r3]");
    const bmR2    = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-bm-r2]");
    const ent2    = ["2a", "2b", "2c", "2d"].map((k) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-ent-${k}]`));
    const ent3    = ["3a", "3b"].map((k) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-ent-${k}]`));
    const entFinal = svg.querySelector("[data-1g-ent-final]");
    const cbPh    = Array.from({ length: 4 }, (_, i) =>
      svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-cb="ph${i}"]`));
    const cbR1    = svg.querySelector('[data-1g-cb="r1"]');
    const cbR3    = svg.querySelector('[data-1g-cb="r3"]');
    const cbR2    = svg.querySelector('[data-1g-cb="r2"]');
    const stepEls = Array.from(fig.querySelectorAll("[data-1g-step]"));

    // ---------------- Loss-toggle scaffolding ----------------
    // Currently disabled — successP = 1.0 means every attempt heralds
    // first try, so the cycle is deterministic and plays linearly.
    // When ready to show loss: flip lossEnabled to true and drop the
    // success probabilities; the animation loop will spend extra cycles
    // showing photons disappear without herald, etc.
    const CONFIG = {
      lossEnabled: false,
      egSuccessP:  1.0,   // P(herald) per EG attempt; ~0.5 realistic
      esSuccessP:  1.0,   // P(success) per matter-qubit BSM; ~0.95 realistic
    };
    function attempt(p) {
      return CONFIG.lossEnabled ? (Math.random() < p) : true;
    }

    // Per-segment state. Each segment owns its own attempt counter and
    // last-outcome flag. With successP = 1.0 attempts always succeed
    // and the phase advances immediately; with lower successP, the
    // animation can spin in the current phase until allSettled() is
    // true. (Retry rendering is scaffolded but not yet active.)
    const egSegs = [0,1,2,3].map(() => ({ heralded: false, attempts: 0 }));
    const es1Segs = ["R1", "R3"].map(() => ({ done: false, attempts: 0 }));
    const es2Segs = ["R2"].map(() => ({ done: false, attempts: 0 }));
    function resetSegs() {
      egSegs.forEach((s) => { s.heralded = false; s.attempts = 0; });
      es1Segs.forEach((s) => { s.done = false; s.attempts = 0; });
      es2Segs.forEach((s) => { s.done = false; s.attempts = 0; });
    }
    function rollPhase1() { egSegs.forEach((s) => { s.attempts++; s.heralded = attempt(CONFIG.egSuccessP); }); }
    function rollPhase2() { es1Segs.forEach((s) => { s.attempts++; s.done = attempt(CONFIG.esSuccessP); }); }
    function rollPhase3() { es2Segs.forEach((s) => { s.attempts++; s.done = attempt(CONFIG.esSuccessP); }); }

    function setOpacity(el, op) { el && el.setAttribute("opacity", String(op)); }
    function setPos(el, x, y) { el && el.setAttribute("cx", String(x)); el && el.setAttribute("cy", String(y)); }
    function highlightStep(n) {
      for (const el of stepEls) {
        el.classList.toggle("sw-step--active", Number(el.dataset["1gStep"]) === n);
      }
    }

    // Photon home positions and their target pBSM input ports (read off
    // the photon-flight dashed paths in the SVG markup).
    const PHOTON_HOME = [
      { x: 130, y: 105 }, { x: 316, y: 105 }, { x: 340, y: 105 }, { x: 522, y: 105 },
      { x: 546, y: 105 }, { x: 728, y: 105 }, { x: 752, y: 105 }, { x: 938, y: 105 },
    ];
    const PHOTON_END = [
      { x: 204.72, y: 152.03 }, { x: 241.28, y: 152.03 },
      { x: 412.72, y: 152.03 }, { x: 449.28, y: 152.03 },
      { x: 618.72, y: 152.03 }, { x: 655.28, y: 152.03 },
      { x: 826.72, y: 152.03 }, { x: 863.28, y: 152.03 },
    ];

    // Classical-bit pulse geometry. EG: from each pBSM midpoint up to
    // y=120 (just below the matter row). ES1: R₁ → A (rightward to
    // leftward), R₃ → B. ES2: R₂ → B.
    const CB_PATHS = {
      ph0: { from: { x: 223, y: 145 }, to: { x: 223, y: 120 } },
      ph1: { from: { x: 431, y: 145 }, to: { x: 431, y: 120 } },
      ph2: { from: { x: 637, y: 145 }, to: { x: 637, y: 120 } },
      ph3: { from: { x: 845, y: 145 }, to: { x: 845, y: 120 } },
      // Both r1 and r3 ship rightward to B; r1 at y=345 (long path)
      // sits below r3 at y=325 so the two travelling pulses don't
      // overlap. Matches the "compose all corrections at B" convention.
      r1:  { from: { x: 354, y: 345 }, to: { x: 927, y: 345 } },
      r3:  { from: { x: 766, y: 325 }, to: { x: 927, y: 325 } },
      r2:  { from: { x: 560, y: 455 }, to: { x: 927, y: 455 } },
    };
    function moveCbAlong(key, t) {
      const el = key.startsWith("ph") ? cbPh[Number(key.slice(2))] :
                 key === "r1" ? cbR1 : key === "r3" ? cbR3 : cbR2;
      const p = CB_PATHS[key];
      const x = p.from.x + (p.to.x - p.from.x) * t;
      const y = p.from.y + (p.to.y - p.from.y) * t;
      el.setAttribute("cx", String(x));
      el.setAttribute("cy", String(y));
    }

    function ease(t) {
      return t < 0.5 ? 4*t*t*t : 1 - Math.pow(-2*t + 2, 3) / 2;
    }

    const reducedMotion = matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)").matches;

    if (reducedMotion) {
      // Static end state: all rows fully visible.
      rows.forEach((r) => setOpacity(r, 1));
      ent2.forEach((e) => e && e.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0"));
      ent3.forEach((e) => e && e.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0"));
      entFinal && entFinal.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0");
      highlightStep(4);
    } else {
      const T_EG_EMIT   = 1400;   // photons emit + travel toward pBSMs
      const T_EG_MEAS   =  900;   // pBSMs pulse, herald bulbs flash
      const T_EG_CLASS  = 1200;   // classical herald travels back up
      const T_ES1_PREP  =  600;   // entanglement curves trace in (row 2)
      const T_ES1_BSM   =  900;   // BM boxes at R₁, R₃ pulse
      const T_ES1_CLASS = 1500;   // 2 classical bits travel outward
      const T_ES2_PREP  =  600;   // entanglement curves trace in (row 3)
      const T_ES2_BSM   =  900;   // BM box at R₂ pulses
      const T_ES2_CLASS = 1500;   // classical bit travels to B
      const T_RESULT    = 1400;   // long A↔B Bell pair traces in
      const T_HOLD      = 2200;
      const T_PAUSE     =  400;
      const PHASE1 = T_EG_EMIT + T_EG_MEAS + T_EG_CLASS;
      const PHASE2 = T_ES1_PREP + T_ES1_BSM + T_ES1_CLASS;
      const PHASE3 = T_ES2_PREP + T_ES2_BSM + T_ES2_CLASS;
      const PHASE4 = T_RESULT;
      const T_TOTAL = PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3 + PHASE4 + T_HOLD + T_PAUSE;

      let running = false;
      let paused = false;
      let cycleStart = 0;
      let pausedAt = 0;

      // mp-wave handles (matter-photon entanglement at top of EG row).
      // Tagged via data-1g-mp-wave="0".."7" — they fade out as the
      // photons are consumed by their respective pBSMs.
      const mpWaves = Array.from({ length: 8 }, (_, i) =>
        svg.querySelector(`[data-1g-mp-wave="${i}"]`));

      // Phase boundaries used by the step controls. Stepping snaps the
      // virtual clock to one of these; the user gets four discrete
      // "frames" of the protocol — start of EG, start of 1st ES,
      // start of 2nd ES, start of Result — plus the hold state.
      const PHASE_STARTS = [
        0,
        PHASE1,
        PHASE1 + PHASE2,
        PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3,
        PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3 + PHASE4,
      ];

      function pickCycleParams() {
        resetSegs();
        rollPhase1();
        rollPhase2();
        rollPhase3();
      }

      function phaseAt(elapsed) {
        if (elapsed < PHASE1) return "EG";
        if (elapsed < PHASE1 + PHASE2) return "1st ES";
        if (elapsed < PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3) return "2nd ES";
        if (elapsed < PHASE1 + PHASE2 + PHASE3 + PHASE4) return "Result";
        return "Hold";
      }

      // Pure render — sets element states based on a virtual elapsed
      // time in [0, T_TOTAL]. No requestAnimationFrame, no time math
      // beyond what's needed for sub-phase interpolation. The transport
      // controls call this with arbitrary clock positions.
      function renderAt(elapsed) {
        let t0 = 0;
        // -------- Phase 1 — EG --------
        if (elapsed < (t0 += PHASE1)) {
          highlightStep(1);
          setOpacity(rows[0], 1);
          setOpacity(rows[1], 0.22);
          setOpacity(rows[2], 0.22);
          setOpacity(rows[3], 0.22);
          ent2.forEach((e) => e && e.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "1"));
          ent3.forEach((e) => e && e.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "1"));
          entFinal && entFinal.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "1");

          const local = elapsed - (t0 - PHASE1);
          if (local < T_EG_EMIT) {
            // 1a: photons fly from matter qubits to pBSM input ports.
            const t = local / T_EG_EMIT;
            const e = ease(t);
            photons.forEach((ph, i) => {
              if (!ph) return;
              const h = PHOTON_HOME[i], en = PHOTON_END[i];
              setPos(ph, h.x + (en.x - h.x) * e, h.y + (en.y - h.y) * e);
              setOpacity(ph, 1);
            });
            mpWaves.forEach((w) => setOpacity(w, 1));
            pbsmPulse.forEach((p) => setOpacity(p, 0));
            heralds.forEach((h) => setOpacity(h, 0));
            cbPh.forEach((c) => setOpacity(c, 0));
          } else if (local < T_EG_EMIT + T_EG_MEAS) {
            // 1b: photons consumed at pBSMs; pulse boxes flash;
            // mp-waves fade (photons gone, matter–photon entanglement
            // collapsed); herald bulbs fade in.
            const t = (local - T_EG_EMIT) / T_EG_MEAS;
            photons.forEach((ph, i) => {
              setOpacity(ph, Math.max(0, 1 - t * 2));
              const en = PHOTON_END[i];
              setPos(ph, en.x, en.y);
            });
            mpWaves.forEach((w) => setOpacity(w, Math.max(0, 1 - t * 2)));
            const pulse = Math.sin(t * Math.PI);
            pbsmPulse.forEach((p, i) => {
              if (!egSegs[i].heralded) return;
              setOpacity(p, pulse);
            });
            heralds.forEach((h, i) => {
              if (!egSegs[i].heralded) return;
              setOpacity(h, Math.min(1, t * 2));
            });
          } else {
            // 1c: classical herald travels from pBSM up toward matter row.
            const t = (local - T_EG_EMIT - T_EG_MEAS) / T_EG_CLASS;
            photons.forEach((ph) => setOpacity(ph, 0));
            mpWaves.forEach((w) => setOpacity(w, 0));
            pbsmPulse.forEach((p) => setOpacity(p, 0));
            heralds.forEach((h, i) => {
              if (!egSegs[i].heralded) return;
              setOpacity(h, Math.max(0.4, 1 - t * 0.5));
            });
            cbPh.forEach((c, i) => {
              if (!egSegs[i].heralded) return;
              setOpacity(c, 1);
              moveCbAlong(`ph${i}`, t);
            });
          }
        }
        // -------- Phase 2 — 1st ES --------
        else if (elapsed < (t0 += PHASE2)) {
          highlightStep(2);
          setOpacity(rows[0], 0.45);
          setOpacity(rows[1], 1);
          setOpacity(rows[2], 0.22);
          setOpacity(rows[3], 0.22);
          mpWaves.forEach((w) => setOpacity(w, 0));
          cbPh.forEach((c) => setOpacity(c, 0));
          heralds.forEach((h) => setOpacity(h, 0));

          const local = elapsed - (t0 - PHASE2);
          if (local < T_ES1_PREP) {
            const t = local / T_ES1_PREP;
            const e = ease(t);
            ent2.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", String(1 - e)));
            setOpacity(cbR1, 0); setOpacity(cbR3, 0);
          } else if (local < T_ES1_PREP + T_ES1_BSM) {
            ent2.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0"));
            const t = (local - T_ES1_PREP) / T_ES1_BSM;
            const pulse = Math.sin(t * Math.PI);
            const w = 1.2 + 2.8 * pulse;
            if (bmR1) bmR1.setAttribute("stroke-width", String(w));
            if (bmR3) bmR3.setAttribute("stroke-width", String(w));
          } else {
            if (bmR1) bmR1.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.2");
            if (bmR3) bmR3.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.2");
            const t = (local - T_ES1_PREP - T_ES1_BSM) / T_ES1_CLASS;
            setOpacity(cbR1, 1); setOpacity(cbR3, 1);
            moveCbAlong("r1", t);
            moveCbAlong("r3", t);
          }
        }
        // -------- Phase 3 — 2nd ES --------
        else if (elapsed < (t0 += PHASE3)) {
          highlightStep(3);
          setOpacity(rows[0], 0.45);
          setOpacity(rows[1], 0.45);
          setOpacity(rows[2], 1);
          setOpacity(rows[3], 0.22);
          setOpacity(cbR1, 0); setOpacity(cbR3, 0);

          const local = elapsed - (t0 - PHASE3);
          if (local < T_ES2_PREP) {
            const t = local / T_ES2_PREP;
            const e = ease(t);
            ent3.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", String(1 - e)));
            setOpacity(cbR2, 0);
          } else if (local < T_ES2_PREP + T_ES2_BSM) {
            ent3.forEach((p) => p && p.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0"));
            const t = (local - T_ES2_PREP) / T_ES2_BSM;
            const pulse = Math.sin(t * Math.PI);
            const w = 1.2 + 2.8 * pulse;
            if (bmR2) bmR2.setAttribute("stroke-width", String(w));
          } else {
            if (bmR2) bmR2.setAttribute("stroke-width", "1.2");
            const t = (local - T_ES2_PREP - T_ES2_BSM) / T_ES2_CLASS;
            setOpacity(cbR2, 1);
            moveCbAlong("r2", t);
          }
        }
        // -------- Phase 4 — Result --------
        else if (elapsed < (t0 += PHASE4)) {
          highlightStep(4);
          setOpacity(rows[0], 0.45);
          setOpacity(rows[1], 0.45);
          setOpacity(rows[2], 0.45);
          setOpacity(rows[3], 1);
          setOpacity(cbR2, 0);
          const t = (elapsed - (t0 - PHASE4)) / PHASE4;
          const e = ease(t);
          entFinal && entFinal.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", String(1 - e));
        }
        // -------- Hold --------
        else if (elapsed < T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE) {
          highlightStep(4);
          rows.forEach((r) => setOpacity(r, 1));
          entFinal && entFinal.setAttribute("stroke-dashoffset", "0");
        } else if (elapsed < T_TOTAL) {
          const t = (elapsed - (T_TOTAL - T_PAUSE)) / T_PAUSE;
          setOpacity(rows[0], 1 - t * 0.8);
          setOpacity(rows[1], 1 - t * 0.8);
          setOpacity(rows[2], 1 - t * 0.8);
        }
        updatePhaseLabel(elapsed);
      }

      // -------- Transport controls --------
      const btnPlay = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-ctl="play"]');
      const btnBack = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-ctl="back"]');
      const btnFwd  = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-ctl="fwd"]');
      const phaseLbl = fig.querySelector('[data-1g-phase]');

      function updatePhaseLabel(elapsed) {
        if (phaseLbl) phaseLbl.textContent = phaseAt(elapsed);
      }
      function setPlayIcon() {
        if (btnPlay) {
          btnPlay.textContent = paused ? "▶" : "⏸";
          btnPlay.setAttribute("aria-label", paused ? "Play" : "Pause");
        }
      }
      function currentElapsed(now) {
        if (paused) return pausedAt;
        let e = now - cycleStart;
        if (e >= T_TOTAL) {
          // wrap inside frame() — but if asked here, normalise.
          e = e % T_TOTAL;
        }
        return e;
      }
      function togglePlay() {
        if (paused) {
          // Resume: shift cycleStart so elapsed reads pausedAt now.
          paused = false;
          cycleStart = performance.now() - pausedAt;
        } else {
          // Pause: freeze the current elapsed value.
          paused = true;
          pausedAt = performance.now() - cycleStart;
          if (pausedAt < 0) pausedAt = 0;
          if (pausedAt >= T_TOTAL) pausedAt = T_TOTAL - 1;
        }
        setPlayIcon();
      }
      function seekTo(t) {
        paused = true;
        pausedAt = Math.max(0, Math.min(T_TOTAL - 1, t));
        renderAt(pausedAt);
        setPlayIcon();
      }
      function stepForward() {
        const cur = currentElapsed(performance.now());
        const eps = 50;  // skip past the current boundary if we're right on one
        for (const b of PHASE_STARTS) {
          if (b > cur + eps) return seekTo(b);
        }
        // already past last phase start — wrap to start.
        seekTo(0);
      }
      function stepBackward() {
        const cur = currentElapsed(performance.now());
        const eps = 50;
        for (let i = PHASE_STARTS.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
          if (PHASE_STARTS[i] < cur - eps) return seekTo(PHASE_STARTS[i]);
        }
        seekTo(PHASE_STARTS[PHASE_STARTS.length - 1]);
      }
      if (btnPlay) btnPlay.addEventListener("click", togglePlay);
      if (btnFwd)  btnFwd.addEventListener("click", stepForward);
      if (btnBack) btnBack.addEventListener("click", stepBackward);
      setPlayIcon();

      function frame(now) {
        if (paused) {
          // Hold the paused frame; keep ticking so unpausing resumes
          // cleanly without a stale render.
          renderAt(pausedAt);
        } else if (running) {
          let elapsed = now - cycleStart;
          if (elapsed >= T_TOTAL) {
            cycleStart = now;
            pickCycleParams();
            elapsed = 0;
          }
          renderAt(elapsed);
        }
        requestAnimationFrame(frame);
      }

      pickCycleParams();
      const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
        for (const entry of entries) {
          if (entry.isIntersecting && !running) {
            running = true;
            cycleStart = performance.now();
            pickCycleParams();
            requestAnimationFrame(frame);
          } else if (!entry.isIntersecting) {
            // Don't fully stop — user may have paused intentionally.
            // Only halt the auto-advance when the user hasn't paused.
            if (!paused) running = false;
          }
        }
      });
      observer.observe(fig);
    }
  }
</script>

